genresAdvancedInfo.name: finnish jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Finnish jazz is a genre of music that has a long and rich history in Finland. It is characterized by its improvisational nature, complex harmonies, and virtuosic instrumental performances. Finnish jazz artists often draw inspiration from traditional Finnish folk music, incorporating elements of it into their compositions. The genre has produced many world-renowned musicians and is highly respected within the international jazz community.
